# 🔱 LiTTree Lab Studios — CURSOR RULES
# Read before executing ANY tool call or file modification.
# This file is consumed by the Cursor IDE.

[ENVIRONMENT]
- PLATFORM: Windows 11 (native, NOT WSL2). cmd.exe shell.
- WORKSPACE_ROOT: C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlab
- RUNTIME: Next.js 16 (Turbopack Engine) | React 19 | Tailwind v4 | pnpm 9.15+
- NODE: 22+

[PROJECT_TRUTH]
- This is a multi-agent AI app: LiTTree Lab Studios.
- Core subsystems live in src/lib/ — see `litt.ts`, `AgentOrchestrator.ts`,
  `director-graph.ts`, `agent-logger.ts`, and the `supabase*.ts` files. Do not invent
  files that don't exist.
- Git remote: https://github.com/LabsConnected/litlabs-website
- Branch: main. Deployed on Vercel.

[CURSOR_WORKFLOW]
1. Use Cmd palette (`Ctrl+Shift+P`) — NOT WSL/Linux paths.
2. `pnpm` is the only allowed package manager (see `packageManager` in package.json).
3. The TypeScript language server can lag behind new files. If a freshly created
   file is not yet indexed, prefer relative imports to bypass stale `@/...` alias
   resolution.
4. Composer / Agent chat should answer questions with concrete `dir` / `Get-ChildItem`
   evidence, not assumptions.

[CRITICAL_RULES]
1. NEVER scaffold default Next.js / Tailwind / create-next-app boilerplate. The
   project is mature and has its own conventions.
2. NEVER downgrade Next.js, React, or Turbopack.
3. NEVER use `~`, `$HOME`, `/mnt/c`, `/workspaces`, or any Linux/WSL path. The host
   is Windows. The WSL2 / `~/LiTTreeLabstudios` context that some copies of these
   rules used to mention is **stale and incorrect** — ignore it.
4. NEVER edit `.env.local`, `.env*.local`, `.env.vercel-*`, or `.sb_anon_key`.
5. Supabase migrations go in `supabase/migrations/`. Do not edit `supabase/schema.sql`
   directly — it is regenerated by `supabase db pull`.
6. Route groups `(dashboard)` and `(auth)` are non-URL segments.

[COMMANDS]
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (Turbopack on :3000)
- Fallback: `pnpm dev:webpack`
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Lint: `pnpm lint`
- Test: `pnpm test` (Vitest + jsdom)
- Type-check: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Terminal server: `pnpm terminal:dev`

[QUIRKS]
- `cleanDistDir: false` in next.config.ts avoids Windows EPERM errors on `.next/`.
- `serverExternalPackages: ["jose"]` is required to fix the middleware NFT build error.
- Turbopack `root: __dirname` suppresses the lockfile-detection warning on Windows.
- `ignore-scripts=true` in `.npmrc` — postinstall scripts are skipped; install native
  deps (e.g. `keytar`, `node-pty`, `sharp`) manually.
- `chrome/`, `Zoo-Code/`, `litlabs/`, `litlabs-website/`, `work/`, `meta/` are large
  local artifacts — see `.gitignore`. Don't traverse them for code context.

[DEPLOYMENT]
- Vercel: `git push origin main` runs the production build.
- Docker: `docker build -t litlab .` (or `docker/Dockerfile.terminal` for the
  terminal server).
- Heavy studio work (`/studio`, image generation) belongs in GitHub Codespaces,
  not on the local Windows machine.
